Title: Whirlpool — Made for the Counter
Author: wavelet-director

INT. SUNLIT KITCHEN - DAWN

A vintage cream-enamel tilt-head stand mixer sits alone on a marble counter. Morning light rakes across its glossy curves. Steam drifts from a kettle just out of frame.

CUT TO:

INT. KITCHEN COUNTER - CLOSE - DAY

The whisk attachment turns slowly inside a polished steel bowl. Soft peaks of meringue lift and fold. A single drop of vanilla extract falls from above and is swallowed by the cream.

CUT TO:

INT. KITCHEN - WIDE - GOLDEN HOUR

The mixer at rest. A loaf of fresh bread cools on a board beside it. Flour dust hangs in a beam of late sun. The kitchen is quiet, lived-in, loved.

FADE OUT.
